# Frontend Conventions (React Native + TypeScript)

## Component Rules

- Use **functional components only** — no class components
- All components must be typed with TypeScript (`React.FC` or explicit props interface)
- File name matches component name: `IngredientCard.tsx` exports `IngredientCard`

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
interface IngredientCardProps {
  name: string;
  quantity: number;
  inStock: boolean;
}

export const IngredientCard: React.FC<IngredientCardProps> = ({ name, quantity, inStock }) => {
  return <View>...</View>;
};

// ❌ BAD — anonymous default export, no types
export default ({ name }) => <View />;
```

## Naming Conventions

| Type            | Convention   | Example              |
| --------------- | ------------ | -------------------- |
| Component file  | PascalCase   | `IngredientCard.tsx` |
| Screen file     | PascalCase   | `RecipeScreen.tsx`   |
| Hook file       | camelCase    | `useIngredients.ts`  |
| Utility file    | camelCase    | `formatDistance.ts`  |

## Hooks

- Extract reusable state logic into `src/hooks/`
- Hook names always start with `use`

```ts
// src/hooks/useIngredients.ts
export function useIngredients(recipeId: string) {
  // fetch, filter, return state
}
```

## API Calls

- **Never call APIs directly from a component or hook**
- All HTTP requests go through `src/services/`

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — src/services/recipeService.ts
export async function fetchIngredients(recipeId: string) {
  const { data } = await apiClient.get(`/recipes/${recipeId}/ingredients`);
  return data;
}

// ❌ BAD — axios call inside a component
const res = await axios.get('/recipes/...');
```

## State Management

- Use **Zustand** for global state (`src/store/`)
- Use `@tanstack/react-query` for server state (fetching, caching)
- Local component state stays in `useState`
